This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on object detection for robot guidance. It also involves the use of neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of transfer learning and depthwise separable convolutions, which are common techniques in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of a meta neural network to allocate object detection neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
